description: A JavaScript library for building user interfaces
author: Facebook
description_long: React is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces. It lets you compose complex UIs from small and isolated pieces of code called 'components'. React has a few different kinds of components, but we'll start with React.Component subclasses:

author: Evan You
description_long: Vue (pronounced /vjuÀê/, like view) is a progressive framework for building user interfaces. Unlike other monolithic frameworks, Vue is designed from the ground up to be incrementally adoptable.

author: Rich Harris
description_long: Svelte is a radical new approach to building user interfaces. Whereas traditional frameworks like React and Vue do the bulk of their work in the browser, Svelte shifts that work into a compile step that happens when you build your app.

author: Evan You
description_long: Vite (French word for 'quick', pronounced /vit/) is a build tool that aims to provide a faster and leaner development experience for modern web projects.

author: Vercel
description_long: Next.js is a React framework that gives you building blocks to create web applications. By framework, we mean Next.js handles the tooling and configuration needed for React, and provides additional structure, features, and optimizations for your application.

author: Oven
description_long: Bun is an all-in-one JavaScript runtime & toolkit designed for speed, complete with a bundler, test runner, and Node.js-compatible package manager.

description: Build smaller, faster, and more secure desktop applications with a web frontend
author: Tauri Contributors
description_long: Tauri is a framework for building tiny, blazingly fast binaries for all major desktop platforms. Developers can integrate any front-end framework that compiles to HTML, JS and CSS for building their user interface.

description: The next-gen web framework. The framework for the modern web. Built on Deno.
author: Deno Land Inc.
description_long: Fresh is a next-gen web framework, built for speed, reliability, and simplicity. Fresh has no build step and sends zero JavaScript to the client by default.

author: Nuxt.js Team
description_long: Nuxt 3 is the latest version of the intuitive Vue framework that makes web development simple and powerful. It provides out-of-the-box features like server-side rendering, static site generation, and more.

author: Svelte Contributors
description_long: SvelteKit is a framework for building web applications of all sizes, with a beautiful development experience and flexible filesystem-based routing.

description: The HTML-first framework. Instant loading web apps.
author: Builder.io
description_long: Qwik is an open-source front-end JavaScript framework for building web applications that load instantly. It achieves this by using resumable JavaScript instead of hydration.

description: Build faster websites with less JavaScript
author: Astro Contributors
description_long: Astro is an all-in-one web framework for building fast, content-focused websites. It brings together the best parts of your favorite frontend frameworks and tools.

description: TypeScript ORM that feels like writing SQL
author: Drizzle Team
description_long: Drizzle ORM is a TypeScript ORM that feels like writing SQL. It is fully type-safe, has a SQL-like syntax, and works with PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite, and more.

description: Next-generation ORM for Node.js and TypeScript
author: Prisma
description_long: Prisma is a next-generation ORM that makes working with databases easy for application developers. It offers type-safe database access, migrations, and a beautiful query interface.

description: Email for developers. Deliver transactional emails at scale.
author: Resend Labs
description_long: Resend is a developer-focused email platform that makes sending transactional emails simple. It offers a clean API, email templates, and detailed analytics.
